# Phase 3.5: Deeper GitHub Auditing Plan

## Goal Description
Enhance the [GitHubAuditorTool](file:///Users/malik/Desktop/SkillSync_Student_Backend/services.py#67-88) to move beyond simple syntax checks. We will fetch the actual file structure and key code samples from a student's GitHub repository and use DeepSeek-V3 to provide qualitative feedback on their "Prime Directive" adherence (Design Patterns, Clean Code, No Plagiarism).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> To avoid rate limits and handle large repos, we will only fetch the **README** and **top-level file structure** initially, then let the agent decide which files to "deep dive" into.

## Proposed Changes

### Infrastructure
#### [MODIFY] [requirements.txt](file:///Users/malik/Desktop/SkillSync_Student_Backend/requirements.txt)
- Add `PyGithub`.

### Tool Enhancement
#### [MODIFY] [services.py](file:///Users/malik/Desktop/SkillSync_Student_Backend/services.py)
- Update [GitHubAuditorTool](file:///Users/malik/Desktop/SkillSync_Student_Backend/services.py#67-88) to use `PyGithub`.
- Implement a `summarize_repo` method that fetches file names and README content.
- Implement an `ai_audit` method that sends this summary to DeepSeek.

### Node Update
#### [MODIFY] [graph.py](file:///Users/malik/Desktop/SkillSync_Student_Backend/graph.py)
- Update [audit_github_node](file:///Users/malik/Desktop/SkillSync_Student_Backend/graph.py#26-39) to call the new async auditing methods.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- Test with a known project (e.g., your own `SkillSync` repo if public, or a sample one).
- Verify that the `github_report` now contains structured insights instead of a placeholder.
